# Setup Guide — Gmail AI Sorter

This guide explains how to install, configure, and run the Gmail AI Sorter project using n8n and Google Gemini AI.

---

# Overview

The workflow automatically:

* Monitors incoming Gmail emails
* Uses Gemini AI to classify emails
* Categorizes emails into:

  * Meeting
  * CheckLater
  * JobVacancy
* Applies Gmail labels automatically

---

# Prerequisites

Before starting, ensure you have:

* Gmail account
* Google Gemini API key
* n8n installed
* Internet connection

---

# Step 1 — Install n8n

## Option A — n8n Cloud

Official Website:

urln8n Cloud[https://n8n.io/cloud/](https://n8n.io/cloud/)

Create an account and login.

---

## Option B — Local Installation Using Docker

Install Docker first.

Run:

```bash
docker run -it --rm \
  -p 5678:5678 \
  -v ~/.n8n:/home/node/.n8n \
  n8nio/n8n
```

Open:

```text
http://localhost:5678
```

---

# Step 2 — Create Gmail Labels

Inside Gmail create the following labels:

```text
Meeting
CheckLater
JobVacancy
```

## How to Create Labels

1. Open Gmail
2. Left sidebar → More
3. Click:

```text
Create new label
```

4. Create labels one by one

---

# Step 3 — Generate Gemini API Key

Open:

urlGoogle AI Studio[https://aistudio.google.com/](https://aistudio.google.com/)

## Steps

1. Login with Google account
2. Click:

```text
Get API Key
```

3. Generate API key
4. Copy and save the key

---

# Step 4 — Create New Workflow in n8n

## Steps

1. Open n8n
2. Click:

```text
New Workflow
```

3. Rename workflow:

```text
Gmail AI Sorter
```

---

# Step 5 — Add Gmail Trigger Node

## Add Node

Search:

```text
Gmail Trigger
```

---

## Configure Gmail Credentials

1. Click:

```text
Create New Credential
```

2. Sign into Gmail
3. Allow permissions

---

## Configure Node

| Field     | Value   |
| --------- | ------- |
| Resource  | Message |
| Operation | Watch   |
| Label     | INBOX   |
| Simplify  | Enabled |

---

# Step 6 — Add Gemini AI Node

## Add Node

Search:

```text
Google Gemini Chat Model
```

---

## Configure Credentials

Paste your Gemini API key.

Save credentials.

---

# Step 7 — Add Basic LLM Chain

## Add Node

Search:

```text
Basic LLM Chain
```

Connect:

```text
Gmail Trigger → Basic LLM Chain
```

Attach Gemini model to the chain.

---

# Step 8 — Configure AI Prompt

Inside Basic LLM Chain use:

```text
You are an intelligent email classifier.

Classify the email into ONLY one category:

- Meeting
- CheckLater
- JobVacancy

Rules:
- Meeting = interviews, calls, appointments
- CheckLater = newsletters, promotions
- JobVacancy = hiring, recruitment
```
